-- Slovak Current-Account Deficit Widens to $581 Million in August, Bank Says
-- B y   R a d o s l a v   T o m e k
-- 2010-10-27T07:58:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-27/slovak-current-account-deficit-widens-to-581-million-in-august.html
Slovakia posted a  current-account 
deficit of 421 million euros ($581.3 million) in August compared
with a revised gap of 328 million euros in the previous month,
the central bank said on its  website  today.  The eight-month shortfall widened to 1.34 billion euros
from a deficit of 1.23 billion euros in the same period last
year, Bratislava, Slovakia-based Narodna Banka Slovenska said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Radoslav Tomek  in Bratislava at 
 rtomek@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net . 